## TASK 2 — ZRAM / Memory Compression Kernel Tuning

### Why
`vm.page-cluster=0` makes the kernel read individual swap pages instead of
clusters. For ZRAM (compressed RAM swap), clusters waste memory bandwidth
reading pages you don't need. Setting it to 0 means only the exact page
requested is decompressed — lower latency, lower memory bandwidth per swap hit.

`kernel.sched_migration_cost_ns=5000000` makes the scheduler less eager to
migrate tasks between CPU cores. Task migration has a cost — the migrated
thread's cache lines are cold on the new core. Higher migration cost means
the game thread stays on the same core longer, keeping its L1/L2 cache warm.

### What to implement

In `GuestProgramLauncherComponent.java`, find the existing sysctl block
(already has vm.max_map_count, vm.swappiness, vm.dirty_*) and add
these two lines AFTER the existing sysctl calls:

```bash
sysctl -w vm.page-cluster=0 2>/dev/null;
sysctl -w kernel.sched_migration_cost_ns=5000000 2>/dev/null;
```

These must run inside the same `sh -c "..."` script that already runs the
other sysctls inside the proot container. Do NOT add them to any host-side
code path.

