## TASK 4 — Wine-GE Runtime Option

### Why
Wine-GE is a community build of Wine with hundreds of game-specific patches
that are not in upstream Wine. Many games that crash, have broken cutscenes,
or refuse to launch on stock Wine work perfectly on Wine-GE because Valve's
Proton team maintains these patches specifically for Steam game compatibility.
This gives users an escape hatch for games that don't work with stock Wine
without requiring a full reinstall.

### What to implement

**Step A — Add runtime field to GameProfileOverrides**

In `GameProfileOverrides.kt`, add:
```kotlin
val wineRuntime: WineRuntime = WineRuntime.STOCK

enum class WineRuntime {
    STOCK,   // existing Wine build already in the app
    WINE_GE  // community Wine-GE build
}
```

