## TASK 5 — ProtonDB Compatibility Badges

### Why
ProtonDB aggregates thousands of community reports about which Steam games
work on Linux/Proton and at what quality level. Showing the ProtonDB tier
on game cards tells users immediately which games will work great vs which
need tweaking vs which are broken — before they waste time trying to launch
a known-broken game.

### API

```
GET https://www.protondb.com/api/v1/reports/summaries/{appId}.json
```

Returns JSON with a `tier` field: `platinum`, `gold`, `silver`, `bronze`,
`borked`, or `pending` (not enough reports).

### What to implement

**Step A — ProtonDbRepository**

```kotlin
class ProtonDbRepository @Inject constructor(
    private val httpClient: HttpClient,  // use existing HTTP client in project
    private val gameDao: GameDao         // use existing Room DAO
) {
    suspend fun getTier(appId: Int): ProtonTier {
        // Check Room cache first — refresh if older than 7 days
        val cached = gameDao.getProtonTier(appId)
        if (cached != null && !cached.isStale()) return cached.tier

        return try {
            val response = httpClient.get(
                "https://www.protondb.com/api/v1/reports/summaries/$appId.json"
            )
            val tier = parseProtonTier(response.body<JsonObject>()["tier"]?.jsonPrimitive?.content)
            gameDao.saveProtonTier(appId, tier, System.currentTimeMillis())
            tier
        } catch (e: Exception) {
            cached?.tier ?: ProtonTier.UNKNOWN
        }
    }
}

enum class ProtonTier { PLATINUM, GOLD, SILVER, BRONZE, BORKED, PENDING, UNKNOWN }
```

**Step B — ProtonDB badge composable**

```kotlin
@Composable
fun ProtonBadge(tier: ProtonTier, modifier: Modifier = Modifier) {
    if (tier == ProtonTier.UNKNOWN || tier == ProtonTier.PENDING) return

    val (label, color) = when (tier) {
        ProtonTier.PLATINUM -> "PLATINUM" to gnNeonTeal
        ProtonTier.GOLD     -> "GOLD"     to gnNeonOrange
        ProtonTier.SILVER   -> "SILVER"   to gnTextSecondary
        ProtonTier.BRONZE   -> "BRONZE"   to gnNeonOrange.copy(alpha = 0.6f)
        ProtonTier.BORKED   -> "BORKED"   to gnStatusError
        else -> return
    }

    Box(
        modifier = modifier
            .background(color.copy(alpha = 0.15f), RoundedCornerShape(4.dp))
            .border(1.dp, color.copy(alpha = 0.4f), RoundedCornerShape(4.dp))
            .padding(horizontal = 5.dp, vertical = 2.dp)
    ) {
        Text(
            text = label,
            style = PluviaTypography.labelSmall.copy(
                fontSize = 9.sp,
                letterSpacing = 0.08.sp,
                fontWeight = FontWeight.Bold
            ),
            color = color
        )
    }
}
```

**Step C — Show badge on game cards**

In `LibraryAppItem.kt` inside `GridCardContent`, add the badge overlaid
on the top-left of the cover art (above the scrim):

```kotlin
