```

Also show it in `GameSettingsBottomSheet.kt` near the game title.

**Step D — Fetch on library load**

In `LibraryViewModel` (or equivalent), when the game list loads, launch
background fetches for ProtonDB tiers:
```kotlin
games.forEach { game ->
    launch(Dispatchers.IO) {
        val tier = protonDbRepository.getTier(game.appId)
        _protonTiers.update { it + (game.appId to tier) }
    }
}
```
Use a rate limiter — add a 50ms delay between requests so ProtonDB API
is not hammered with 200 simultaneous requests.

